message: “Sex trafficking is actually very pervasive,” Rep. Mary Kunesh-Podein, DFL-New Brighton, said. She co-authored the legislation. “We can’t just stand idly by thinking that this isn’t happening in our backyard.”

data.description: A bipartisan group of Minnesota lawmakers announced Monday, Jan. 29 they would introduce legislation during the coming 2018 session designed to help prevent sex trafficking in Minnesota through education.
data.title: MN tackles sex trafficking with education
